# Project Rules for AI Contributions

## 1) Project Overview

### Workspace: `zynerd-webapp` (single app)

- Next.js web application for Cerebellum Academy — a **Counselling web app** for medical exam students.
- Flow: Students study for medical exams → take the exam → check which college they got for study (counselling/college selection).
- Features: videos, resources, tools, education details, referrals.
- End users: medical exam students checking counselling results and college allotment after exams.

## 2) Stack & Versions

### Languages / Runtime / Framework

- TypeScript `^5.7.2` (`tsconfig.json` has `strict: true`, `allowJs: true`)
- React `^19.2.3`, React DOM `^19.2.3`
- Next.js `16.0.10` (Pages Router under `src/pages`)
- Node.js: `20` (from CI workflow)

### Major Libraries (from `package.json`)

- State: `@reduxjs/toolkit` `^1.9.5`, `react-redux` `^8.1.1`, `redux-persist` `^6.0.0`
- Data: `axios` `^1.4.0`, `@tanstack/react-query` `^4.32.6`
- UI: `tailwindcss` `^3.2.4`, `@tailwindcss/forms` `^0.5.3`, `@headlessui/react` `^1.7.14`, `@heroicons/react` `^2.0.15`
- Forms: `formik` `^2.4.1`, `yup` `^1.2.0`
- Integrations: `firebase` `^12.7.0`, `react-google-recaptcha-v3` `^1.10.1`
- Other: `dayjs` `^1.11.7`, `react-hot-toast` `^2.4.1`, `swiper` `^12.0.1`, `idb` `^8.0.2`

### Tooling

- Lint: ESLint (`eslint` `^9.17.0`, `eslint-config-next` `16.0.10`, extends `next` + `prettier`)
- Format: Prettier (`^3.4.2`, `.prettierrc.js`, `prettier-plugin-organize-imports`)
- Package manager: Yarn `1.22.22`
- Scripts: `yarn dev`, `yarn build`, `yarn start`, `yarn lint`

## 3) Project Structure

### Layout

- `src/pages` - Next.js Pages Router pages and API routes
- `src/pages/api` - API routes (e.g. `image-proxy.ts`)
- `components` - shared UI and feature components (videos, user-profile, common, global, qbank, etc.)
- `src/hooks` - custom React hooks
- `src/utils` - helpers, API client, validations, config
- `src/types` - TypeScript type definitions
- `src/data` - static JSON data (e.g. `videosData.json`)
- `lib/redux` - store, reducers, slices, typed hooks
- `lib/indexedDB` - IndexedDB modules (image cache, test series store)
- `src/styles`, `src/css` - global styles
- `public` - static assets

### Path Aliases (`tsconfig.json`)

- `@/*` → `./src/*` and `./components/*`

### Entrypoints

- App: `src/pages/_app.tsx`
- Document: `src/pages/_document.tsx`
- API constants: `src/constants.ts`
- Config: `src/utils/config.ts`

## 4) Coding Conventions

### Naming

- Variables/functions: `camelCase`
- Components/types/interfaces: `PascalCase`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g. in `src/constants.ts`)
- File names: mixed (`kebab-case`, `PascalCase`, `camelCase`); preserve local folder style

### React / Components

- Functional components with hooks
- HOC usage (e.g. `withAuth(...)`)
- Use `'use client'` where needed for client components

### Imports

- Prefer `@/*` path aliases
- Both default and named exports used; follow existing file style

### TypeScript

- Strict mode enabled
- Some `any`/`@ts-ignore` exist; match local strictness per file

### Error Handling

- `try/catch` with early returns
- API routes return explicit HTTP status + JSON
- Toast for user feedback (`react-hot-toast`)

## 5) Protected Areas - DO NOT TOUCH

- NEVER read, reference, copy, log, or modify:
  - `.env`, `.env.*`, `config/secrets.*`, `*.pem`, `*.key`, any secret material
- Do not refactor auth modules without explicit instruction:
  - `components/global/WithAuth.tsx`
  - `src/utils/api/authInterceptor.ts`
  - Token flow in `src/utils/api/axios.ts`
- Never modify CI/CD configs: `.github/workflows/**`
- Never edit `yarn.lock` unless dependency changes are requested
- Treat as read-only: `dist/`, `build/`, `node_modules/`, `.next/`

## 6) AI Working Rules

- For tasks touching 3+ files, produce a plan first:
  - files to change
  - intended edit per file
  - risks / what could break
- Do not modify files outside the requested scope
- Preserve existing patterns; prefer minimal diffs over broad refactors
- Never replace working code with placeholders like `// ... rest of logic`
- Ask before adding dependencies or changing versions
- For bug fixes, explain the cause before applying changes
- If uncertain about a project pattern, ask instead of guessing
- After changes, remind user to run: `yarn lint`, `yarn build`, `yarn dev`
